      "Still, the reconstructed state is never neutral, because it is built from my own materials. When I try to empathize with someone I do not build their state from nothing; I use my own memories, my own body, my own past pain, my own imagination, my own assumptions about what the situation means. This is necessary, since without using myself I cannot get close to them at all. But because I use myself, I may also distort them. I may think I understand their sadness because it resembles a sadness I have had, or their fear because I know what fear feels like in me, when their sadness may be structured differently, their fear may come from another history, and their silence may not mean what my silence would.",
